To honor some of its key distributors, retailers and wholesalers across the country, Guinness Nigeria recently awarded prizes to winners of its Elite Promo exercise which kicked off in November 2019 and was concluded in March 2020. <img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter wp-image-858316 size-full" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Pic-5.jpeg" alt="" width="1024" height="683" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Pic-5.jpeg 1024w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Pic-5-300x200.jpeg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"> The brand deemed it fit to reward their International Premium Spirits Distributors who have demonstrated commitment, hard work, dedication to partnership and business excellence thereby contributing to the growth and profitability of Guinness Nigeria. <img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter wp-image-858318 size-full" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Pic-6.jpeg" alt="" width="1024" height="683" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Pic-6.jpeg 1024w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Pic-6-300x200.jpeg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"> Speaking at the presentation of awards, Commercial Director, Guinness Nigeria, Adebayo Alli, said: Guinness Nigeria is committed to recognizing and celebrating excellence which is why we reward individuals who strive to go above and beyond the call of duty. Our distributors are like our support systems and we set up a reward scheme like the Elite promo to encourage them to continue to innovate and reinvent themselves. <img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter wp-image-858317 size-full" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Pic-3.jpeg" alt="" width="678" height="1024" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Pic-3.jpeg 678w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Pic-3-199x300.jpeg 199w" sizes="(max-width: 678px) 100vw, 678px"> The winning distributors, wholesalers and retailers were presented their rewards recently in Port-Harcourt, Abuja and Lagos. Some of the prizes won were a Hyundai Santa FE SUV, a fully detached duplex in a high brow location in Lagos, generator sets and shopping vouchers worth over N200,000. <img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter wp-image-858319 size-full" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Pic-2.jpeg" alt="" width="1024" height="684" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Pic-2.jpeg 1024w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Pic-2-300x200.jpeg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px">